A small church with welcoming, generous people... where all the redeemed are welcome! The island of France and France belong to Jesus! Glory to God!
Personally, I left this church after 3 years. Too bad experiences.

Not at all comfortable it's too Baptism resembling Jehovah. They almost force you to convert. By relaunching yourself. It's because of the appearance of bling bling, they show their wealth instead of remaining discreet and as soon as you don't fit their mold they reject you as less than nothing.

Eglise Paris M√©tropole is also a Church in Lognes, dynamic, welcoming and contemporary. Easy and free parking! Every Sunday 10 a.m. and Thursday 7:30 p.m. Pastor available by appointment. Address: 8 Rue Sainte-Claire D√©ville, 77185 Lognes

I went there for the 9:30 a.m. service. The room was crowded, but I managed to find a seat. I had a good time there, the people are smiling and welcoming. The songs are dynamic and inspired. Always performed by singers who seem to live what they sing. The sermons speak to me. I always come away from these moments enriched. I recommend this church.

The only downside that I could say about this church is that it is a Parisian church, and therefore when you are new, integration is more difficult than a church in the south of France. But apart from that, if you persevere everything is fine! Visit the EPM website for more information on worship times etc.

I was baptized in this church, but no Bible study support after that. Today I feel empty. I don't hear the pastors speaking in tongues, or very little; even less do our sisters and brothers pray in tongues. Where is the Holy Spirit
A very beautiful place of worship. Multicultural; you really feel welcomed there: with a smile and warmth. And most importantly, the presence of God is truly there and the quality teachers.

Beautiful energy of prayer for Jesus, BUT with fundamentalist overtones not cool in the 21st century... Against tolerance, bad Christians (called "cultural"), secularism, marriage for all, etc... Grass is very green but the ground is slippery...
It is a very good church, with a pastoral team eager for the Lord, God is at work. I recommend it to you. God bless you !

A very noisy assembly where believers confuse devotion and hysteria. Here, it's whoever shouts the loudest. Speaking in tongues is extravagant, and there is no one to interpret.  We are therefore very far from St. Paul's recommendations on how worship should take place: praying in turns, speaking in tongues only if there is interpretation, etc.  The stage looks like a TV set with sound system and giant screen, the sound system is deafening and the musicians let loose like in a rock concert. All that's missing is the lighters.  A worldly church, indeed.
It is a warm and blessed place
I really enjoy listening to all the pastors. They allow me to greatly enrich myself with teachings in my walk with God. Be blessed all and glory to God, glory to Jesus whom I adore! Amen.
